# Data Package

`package data` handles persistence, export formats, and OS-level integration.

## File Organization

| File | Concern |
|------|---------|
| `palette.odin` | Load/save palette files, add/remove/reorder |
| `history.odin` | Ring-buffer color history |
| `export.odin` | Export to ASE, GPL, CSS, Tailwind, JSON, PNG, TXT |
| `eyedropper.odin` | OS-level screen capture for color picking |
| `image_extract.odin` | K-means palette extraction from images |

## Conventions

- Palette and history use fixed-size arrays owned by `AppState` — procedures take slices and count pointers: `proc(palette: []rl.Color, count: ^int, ...)`
- Export procedures use stack buffers (`buf: [N]u8`) with manual offset tracking — no heap allocation
- For text export, return `cstring` via `fmt.ctprintf` (temp-allocated). For file export, take a `path: string` parameter and call `os.write_entire_file`
- Platform-specific code uses `when ODIN_OS == .Darwin` / `.Linux` conditional compilation, not runtime checks
- Domain constants (`MAX_PALETTE`, `HISTORY_MAX`, `SWATCH_STRIDE`, `EXTRACT_COUNT`) live in the file that defines the related data structure
- May import `"../color"` for color utilities — never import `"../ui"`
